Class FascinatingNumber

java.lang.Object
FascinatingNumber
public class FascinatingNumber extends Object
A class to determine if user-provided integers are Fibonacci numbers and/or prime numbers. The program takes up to 10 integers from the user and analyzes each one.
Version:
1.0
Author:
Muhammad Ahsan Saleem

    • isPrime

      public static boolean isPrime(int candidate)
      Checks if a given integer is a prime number. An integer is prime if it is greater than 1 and has no positive divisors other than 1 and itself.
      Parameters:
      candidate - The integer to check.
      Returns:
      true if the candidate is a prime number, false otherwise.

    • isFibonacci

      public static boolean isFibonacci(int givenNumber)
      Checks if a given integer is a Fibonacci number. The method generates Fibonacci numbers iteratively and checks if the given number matches any number in the sequence.
      Parameters:
      givenNumber - The integer to check.
      Returns:
      true if the givenNumber is a Fibonacci number, false otherwise.

    • getToFillTheIntegerArray

      public static int getToFillTheIntegerArray(int[] givenArray)
      Prompts the user to enter integers to fill a given array. Input stops when the user enters the sentinel value (0) or when the array is full.
      Parameters:
      givenArray - The integer array to be filled with user input.
      Returns:
      The number of integers the user actually entered (excluding the sentinel value).
